---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, "");
const title = "Privacy — Laydown";
const description =
  "Laydown runs entirely on your device. It has no network code and collects, stores or transmits no personal data.";
const updated = "16 July 2026";
const repo = "https://github.com/danielmevit/laydown";
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="32x32" href={`${base}/assets/icon_32.png`} />
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" sizes="256x256" href={`${base}/assets/icon_256.png`} />
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <meta name="robots" content="index,follow" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://danielmevit.github.io/laydown/privacy/" />

    <style is:global>
      :root {
        --bg: #0a0a0a;
        --bg-soft: #101010;
        --card: #151515;
        --text: #c8c6c3;
        --heading: #ffffff;
        --muted: #8a8784;
        --border: #2a2724;
        --accent: #d07b24;
        --accent-hi: #e8912f;
        --radius: 14px;
      }
      * { box-sizing: border-box; }
      html { scroll-behavior: smooth; }
      body {
        font-family: "Inter", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI", Roboto,
          Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        background: var(--bg);
        color: var(--text);
        line-height: 1.7;
        margin: 0;
        -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      }
      a { color: var(--accent-hi); }
      .wrap { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 1.5rem; }

      nav {
        display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
        padding: 1.1rem 0;
      }
      .brand {
        display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.6rem;
        font-weight: 700; color: var(--heading); text-decoration: none; font-size: 1.15rem;
      }
      .brand img { width: 26px; height: 26px; border-radius: 6px; flex: none; }
      nav a.back { color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 500; font-size: 0.95rem; }
      nav a.back:hover { color: var(--heading); }

      main { padding: 1.5rem 0 4rem; }
      h1 { color: var(--heading); font-size: clamp(1.8rem, 4vw, 2.4rem); margin: 1rem 0 0.3rem; }
      .updated { color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.9rem; margin: 0 0 2rem; }
      h2 { color: var(--heading); font-size: 1.2rem; margin: 2.2rem 0 0.5rem; }
      p { margin: 0.6rem 0; }
      ul { margin: 0.6rem 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; }
      li { margin: 0.3rem 0; }
      .lede {
        background: var(--card); border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent); border-radius: var(--radius);
        padding: 1.1rem 1.3rem; margin: 0 0 1.5rem; color: var(--heading);
      }
      code {
        background: #1c1a18; border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 5px; padding: 1px 6px; font-size: 0.9em; color: var(--text);
      }
      footer {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 1.6rem 0 3rem;
        color: var(--muted); font-size: 0.88rem;
      }
      footer a { color: var(--muted); }
      footer a:hover { color: var(--heading); }
    </style>
  </head>

  <body>
    <div class="wrap">
      <nav>
        <a class="brand" href={`${base}/`}>
          <img src={`${base}/assets/icon_256.png`} alt="" width="26" height="26" /> Laydown
        </a>
        <a class="back" href={`${base}/`}>&larr; Back to Laydown</a>
      </nav>

      <main>
        <h1>Privacy</h1>
        <p class="updated">Last updated {updated}</p>

        <p class="lede">
          Laydown runs entirely on your own computer. It has no network code, no analytics
          and no accounts. It does not collect, store or transmit any personal data — not to
          us, not to anyone. There is nothing to opt out of, because there is nothing being
          gathered.
        </p>

        <h2>What Laydown does with your files</h2>
        <p>
          Laydown opens a PDF you choose, arranges its pages onto a press sheet, and writes a
          new PDF where you tell it to. Your documents are read from and written to your own
          disk, and nowhere else. They are never uploaded, and the app makes no internet
          connection while it works — or at any other time.
        </p>

        <h2>What is stored on your device</h2>
        <p>The only things Laydown keeps are the preferences you set yourself:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Your recent-files list and window preferences, in the Windows registry under
            <code>HKCU\Software\Laydown</code> (macOS and Linux use the platform's standard
            per-user settings location).</li>
          <li>Any imposition <em>presets</em> you save — plain files you place where you
            choose.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          All of this lives on your machine, under your user account. It is never sent
          anywhere. Uninstalling the app, or clearing the recent-files list from within it,
          removes this information.
        </p>

        <h2>No tracking, no third parties</h2>
        <p>
          There is no telemetry, no crash reporting, no advertising, and no third-party
          services embedded in the application. The app does not know who you are and makes no
          attempt to find out.
        </p>

        <h2>This website</h2>
        <p>
          This site is a set of static pages hosted on GitHub Pages. It sets no cookies and
          runs no analytics of its own. It loads the Inter typeface from Google Fonts, which
          may receive your IP address as part of serving those font files — a standard part of
          how web fonts work. If you would rather avoid even that, a browser extension that
          blocks external fonts prevents it, with no effect on the app itself.
        </p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>
          Laydown is a general-purpose tool for print work. It is not directed at children and
          collects no information from anyone, including children.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If this policy ever changes, the new version will be posted on this page with an
          updated date above. Because the app collects nothing, we do not expect the substance
          to change.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions are welcome on the project's
          <a href={`${repo}/issues`}>issue tracker</a>. Laydown is free, open-source software
          (AGPL-3.0); the full source is at <a href={repo}>github.com/danielmevit/laydown</a>,
          so anything stated here can be checked against the code.
        </p>
      </main>

      <footer>
        &copy; 2026 <a href="https://github.com/danielmevit">Daniel Mevit</a> &middot; Made by
        <a href="https://damt.xyz">damt.xyz</a> &middot;
        <a href={`${base}/`}>Home</a>
      </footer>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
